    "recap_headline": "Oregon State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "IRVINE, Calif.\n\u2013 UC Irvine was looking to take its first lead of the series in the eighth Saturday at Cicerone Field. The Anteaters loaded the bases and had no one out down by two.\nThen stepped in\nAlbert Roblez\n.\nThe senior right-hander got out of the bases-loaded jam thanks to an infield fly and a pair of strikeouts, then tossed a scoreless ninth to help Oregon State to a 5-3 win over UC Irvine, clinching the series for the Beavers.\nOSU goes for the sweep Sunday at 1 p.m. PT.\nRoblez made his second career appearance at Cicerone Field, the first coming last season while a member of Long Beach State. He now has two saves at UC Irvine's home turf, going a combined five innings with eight strikeouts.\nHe now also has seven saves as a Beaver.\nRoblez closed out an outing that saw the Beavers (16-5 overall) pull out to another 5-1 lead.\nRyan VandenBrink\ndoubled in a pair of runs in the first. The Anteaters (9-13) scored a solo run in the second before the Beavers plated a pair in the sixth on an RBI single by\nTyler Inge\nand groundout by\nAdam Haight\n.\nJosh Proctor\nlaunched his fourth home run of the season over the fence in left in the seventh to give OSU the four-run advantage. A key advantage after Landon Gaz homered in the seventh to cut the Beavers' lead to two.\nA pair of walks by\nNoah Scott\nand Tanner Doubles and then a bunt single by the Anteaters' Frankie Carney gave UC Irvine a bases-loaded situation with no down. In stepped Roblez, who got Alonso Reyes to pop up and then got out of the jam after striking out Zach Fjelstad and Auggie Gutierrez.\nEthan Kleinschmit\nmade his sixth start of the season for the Beavers, and was sharp through six innings of work. He struck out three \u2013 his first came in the fifth \u2013 while allowing one hit and an unearned run. He gave way to Scott in the seventh, who then combined with Roblez for eight strikeouts in the last three innings.\nProctor paced Oregon State offensively with three hits, including a double. Inge and\nCooper Vance\nhad two apiece.\nOregon State picked up two of its five runs on UC Irvine starter Ricky Ojeda, who went four full. He gave up five hits and struck out six to take the loss and drop to 1-3 on the year.\nOregon State and UC Irvine conclude the three-game series Sunday at Cicerone Field. First pitch is slated for 1 p.m. PT. The game can be heard live on the Beaver Sports Network and watched on ESPN+.\nFollow Us On Social\nFor more information on the Oregon State baseball team, follow the club's official X account at X.com/BeaverBaseball, by Facebook at Facebook.com/OregonStateBaseball, at BeaverBaseball.OSUBeavers.com on BlueSky or on Instagram at Instagram.com/BeaverBaseball.\nOUR MISSION\nOregon State Athletics strives to Build Excellent Authentic Visionary Student-Athletes (Go BEAVS).",
